str2: A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.

str2: (a) I receive, get, (b) I take, lay hold of.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
(a) adj: dead, lifeless, subject to death, mortal, (b) noun: a dead body, a corpse. From an apparently primary nekus; dead.
A rising again, resurrection. From anistemi; a standing up again, i.e. a resurrection from death (its author), or a recovery.
Other, another (of more than two), different. A primary word; 'else, ' i.e. Different.

str2: From a derivative of tupto; to stretch on an instrument of torture resembling a drum, and thus beat to death.

str2: From pros and dechomai; to admit (figuratively) endurance); by implication, to await.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
From a compound of apo and lutron; ransom in full, i.e. riddance, or Christian salvation.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

str2: (a) gen: I obtain, (b) absol: I chance, happen; ordinary, everyday, it may chance, perhaps.
Stronger, more excellent. Comparative of a derivative of kratos; stronger, i.e. better, i.e. Nobler.
